2026-05-31 | Destroying Asteroids

	Question
Return true if all asteroids can be destroyed.
	Key Insight
To maximize the planet's growth,
always destroy the smallest available asteroid first.
Why?
Destroying smaller asteroids increases mass,
making larger asteroids easier to destroy later.
This is a classic greedy strategy.
	Approach
1.	Sort asteroids in ascending order.
2.	Store planet mass in long long
		(to avoid overflow).
3.	Process asteroids from smallest to largest.
4.	If:
		currentMass < asteroid
		return false.
5.	Otherwise:
		currentMass += asteroid.
6.	If all asteroids processed:
		return true.
	Time Complexity
	O(n log n)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    bool asteroidsDestroyed(int mass, vector<int>& asteroids) {
        sort(asteroids.begin(), asteroids.end());
        long long currMass = mass;
        for(int asteroid : asteroids){
            if(currMass < asteroid)
                return false;
            currMass += asteroid;
        }
        return true;
    }
};
	Key Insight
Choosing the smallest asteroid first is always optimal because it gives the maximum chance to increase the planet's mass before facing larger asteroids. After sorting, a single linear scan determines whether all asteroids can be destroyed.
